properties.Name: Hickory Creek Floodplain Management Study
properties.Description: Comprehensive floodplain management study with updated flood mapping and recommendations for improvements

properties.Name: Mill Creek Drainage Relief System - Phase III
properties.Description: Engineering for remainder of creek area ROW, creek restoration, upper basin relief systems, and re-routing of existing system trunk lines that are on private property or crossing mid-block - completes full relief for Mill Creek

properties.Name: Spring Grove 13300 Block
properties.Description: Upgrade drainage system in the area of 13330 Spring Grove Ave to provide flooding relief during the 100-year. Refer to the 2021 AZB Report.

properties.Name: Hymie Circle 10105-10109
properties.Description: Design & Const. - No system on improved street. Current street and gutters no longer have adequate slopes to convey runoff. Add system at the cul-de-sac of Hymie Circle to Masters Road.

properties.Description: Design & Const. of repairs to existing storm sewer system. Install approx. four 14' inlets, 500 LF of 36" RCP, 60 LF of 24" RCP storm laterals on Atlanta St. from MLK Jr. Blvd. to South Blvd.

properties.Name: Woody Branch Erosion Control - Glen Oaks Blvd & Hunters View Group 6

properties.Name: 9728 Springtree Storm Drainage Relief

properties.Name: Cresthaven/Culcourt St Storm Drainage Relief
properties.Description: Design and const. of a storm sewer conveyance system along Cresthaven and Culcourt to prevent runoff from flooding properties along Culcourt.

properties.Name: 10101 Royal Highlands Drainage Improvements
properties.Description: Installation of storm sewer and inlets to provide drainage relief to 10101 Royal Highlands

properties.Name: Royal Spring 10510 Storm Drainage Relief

properties.Name: Pruitt Branch @ C F Hawn
properties.Description: Analysis & Design. Construction will be a future project contingent on agreement/cooperation with TxDOT.  Upsize culvert crossing of C F Hawn US 175 to prevent overtopping as shown by CTP FY19.

properties.Description: Remove and replace existing 24" RCP to new 30 RCP (150 linear feet). Install 10-foot storm inlet to a 21” RCP lateral (100 ft to connect to new 30” RCP).

properties.Name: Weeburn 3677 Storm Drainage Relief
properties.Description: Stormwater runoff bypassing alley and flooding home. Install 10-foot storm inlet and lateral to main system.

properties.Name: East Peaks Upper/Middle Basin Relief System
properties.Description: Continuation of the MCPBST Drainage Relief Tunnel for the East Peaks Upper and Middle basins. Engineering of proposed trunk line as outlined in the 2018 East Peaks Master Drainage Plan.

properties.Name: Bruton Terrace Est. Storm Drainage Relief
properties.Description: Upsize drainage outfall pipes for the Bruton Terrace Est at the intersections of Riverway and Palisade and Riverway and Seaway.

properties.Name: Sanford Ave Relief System (Little Forest Hill) Phase 2
properties.Description: Continuation of the Sanford Ave Relief System project. 100-year drainage improvements from Sanford Ave @ Daytonia to Tavaros @ Forest Hills Blvd.

properties.Name: 5827 Bluffman Storm Drainage Relief
properties.Description: Storm drainage relief at 5827 Bluffman. Analysis, Design, and construction. Current system approx. 5-yr

properties.Name: Reinhart Branch Flood Management Study Update
properties.Description: Floodplain Management study of Reinhart Branch to determine potential capital projects to address flooding, drainage, and erosion.

properties.Description: Update of 1983 Coombs Creek FMS & 2021 Kidd Springs Tunnel TM. Update H&H if needed. Identify new projects, including the evaluation of naturalistic and holistic streambank stabilization and protection, for Coombs Creek and Kidds Springs.
